Below is a worked‐through example of how to interpret and build the two structures exactly as shown, without rotating any blocks beyond the orientations given in the dictionary.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1)  DETAILED ANALYSIS OF THE MAIN TARGET IMAGE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
■ Overall Count and Layers
•  The scene consists of TWO separate sub‐structures.  
•  Total of 13 blocks are used across both.

Structure A (the “arch/house” on the left), 8 blocks total:
  –  Bottom Layer:  
     ➊ Two columns, each made of two blue cubes stacked (4 blue cubes total).  
  –  Middle Layer:  
     ➋ A short yellow rectangular block spans across the two columns.  
     ➌ A yellow half‐cylinder sits in the center, nested under the arch.  
  –  Top Layer:  
     ➍ A red arch block rests above the half‐cylinder.  
     ➎ Finally, a red triangular “roof” block on the very top.  

Structure B (the “car” on the right), 5 blocks total:
  –  Bottom Layer:  
     ➊ Two orange cylinders laid horizontally, acting as wheels.  
  –  Top Layer:  
     ➋ One long yellow rectangular block bridging those two wheels.  
     ➌ A single blue cube sitting on top of the bar (toward one side).  
     ➍ Another yellow half‐cylinder on top of the bar (toward the other side).  

In summary:  
•  Structure A uses 4 blue cubes, 1 red arch, 1 red roof block, 1 short yellow bar, and 1 yellow half‐cylinder.  
•  Structure B uses 2 orange cylinders, 1 long yellow bar, 1 blue cube, and 1 yellow half‐cylinder.  

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2)  SELECTING THE REQUIRED BLOCKS FROM THE DICTIONARY
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
From the block‐index image, the following matches are needed (no re‐orientations allowed):

•  Blue Cube → index 3  
  –  Used FIVE times total (4 in the left arch structure, 1 in the car).  

•  Red Arch (opening facing front) → index 1  
  –  Used ONCE (the arch atop the left structure).  

•  Short Yellow Rectangular Bar (horizontal) → index 4  
  –  Used ONCE (spanning the blue pillars in Structure A).  

•  Long Yellow Rectangular Bar (horizontal) → index 5  
  –  Used ONCE (the main “chassis” in the car).  

•  Orange Cylinder (horizontal) → index 9  
  –  Used TWICE (the two wheels under the car).  

•  Yellow Half‐Cylinder (curved side up, horizontal) → index 10  
  –  Used TWICE (one under the red arch, one on the car’s bar).  

•  Red Triangular “Roof” Block → index 13  
  –  Used ONCE (the rooftop piece above the red arch).  

Block‐Index List (with quantities in parentheses):  
  [1], [3 × 5], [4], [5], [9 × 2], [10 × 2], [13]  

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3)  STEP-BY-STEP ASSEMBLY INSTRUCTIONS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Below is one logical order for placing each piece. Feel free to group or reorder steps if desired, but these 13 moves will reproduce the target exactly:

{
 Step1:  Move block with index 3   // Place 1st blue cube (left column, bottom)
 Step2:  Move block with index 3   // Stack 2nd blue cube on top of the first
 Step3:  Move block with index 3   // Place 3rd blue cube (right column, bottom)
 Step4:  Move block with index 3   // Stack 4th blue cube on top of the third
 Step5:  Move block with index 4   // Place short yellow bar bridging the two blue columns
 Step6:  Move block with index 10  // Set yellow half-cylinder on that bar, centered
 Step7:  Move block with index 1   // Put red arch on top, over the half-cylinder
 Step8:  Move block with index 13  // Add the red triangular roof on very top

 // Now the “car” structure:
 Step9:  Move block with index 9   // Place 1st orange cylinder horizontally (wheel)
 Step10: Move block with index 9   // Place 2nd orange cylinder horizontally (second wheel)
 Step11: Move block with index 5   // Lay long yellow bar atop the two orange wheels
 Step12: Move block with index 3   // Put the 5th blue cube on the bar (forming the “cab”)
 Step13: Move block with index 10  // Place 2nd yellow half-cylinder on the bar (rear “hood”)
}

Following those steps (with the indicated blocks) will exactly reproduce the two structures as shown in the main image.
